# Squad Flight Finder - Environment Variables
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your actual values

# ============================================================================
# AMADEUS API CREDENTIALS (Backend Only - SECURE!)
# ============================================================================
# These credentials are used by Vercel Serverless Functions (backend) and are NOT exposed to the browser
# Get your credentials at: https://developers.amadeus.com/
# 1. Sign up for a free account
# 2. Create a new app
# 3. Copy your API Key and Secret below

AMADEUS_API_KEY=your_api_key_here
AMADEUS_API_SECRET=your_api_secret_here

# ============================================================================
# DEPLOYMENT INSTRUCTIONS
# ============================================================================

# LOCAL DEVELOPMENT:
# 1. Copy this file to .env: cp .env.example .env
# 2. Fill in your Amadeus credentials above
# 3. Run: npm run dev:vercel (uses Vercel Dev to run serverless functions locally)

# VERCEL DEPLOYMENT:
# 1. Connect your repo to Vercel (https://vercel.com)
# 2. Go to: Project Settings > Environment Variables
# 3. Add AMADEUS_API_KEY and AMADEUS_API_SECRET
# 4. (Optional) Add VITE_SENTRY_DSN for error tracking
# 5. Deploy your site
# 6. Credentials stay secure on the server!

# ============================================================================
# NOTES
# ============================================================================
# - No VITE_ prefix! These are backend-only variables
# - The frontend calls /api/* endpoints which proxy to Amadeus
# - API credentials never reach the browser (secure!)
# - Use TEST credentials for development
# - Use PRODUCTION credentials for live deployment

# Security Reminders:
# ✅ Credentials are server-side only (secure!)
# ⚠️ NEVER commit .env to git (it's in .gitignore)
# ⚠️ NEVER share your API keys publicly
# ⚠️ Rotate keys if accidentally exposed
# ⚠️ Use different keys for dev/staging/production
